Babagana Kingibe
        
 








President Muhammadu Buhari has appointed Babagana Kingibe Chief of Staff following the death of Abba Kyari who on Friday and the was buried in Abuja on Saturday.

Abba Kyari tested positive to coronavirus on his return from Germany and subsequently
died of the infection in Lagos.

Kingibe has been acting as Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari since Kyari left the Presidency for treatment.

